Source: cx-gpu-nvidia
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: CX Linux Team <team@cxlinux.ai>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://cxlinux.ai
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/cxlinux-ai/cx-distro
Vcs-Git: https://github.com/cxlinux-ai/cx-distro.git
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: cx-gpu-nvidia
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 cx-core
Recommends:
 nvidia-driver,
 nvidia-kernel-dkms | nvidia-kernel-open-dkms,
 nvidia-smi,
 nvidia-settings,
 nvidia-cuda-toolkit,
 nvidia-container-toolkit,
 libnvidia-ml1,
 libnvidia-compute
Suggests:
 cuda,
 cudnn,
 tensorrt
Provides: cx-gpu-backend
Description: CX Linux NVIDIA GPU enablement
 This meta-package provides NVIDIA GPU support for CX Linux,
 including drivers, CUDA toolkit, and container integration.
 .
 Features:
  - NVIDIA driver (proprietary or open kernel modules)
  - CUDA compute support
  - Container GPU passthrough (nvidia-container-toolkit)
  - GPU monitoring (nvidia-smi)
 .
 For Secure Boot systems:
  - Run 'cx gpu mok-setup' to configure MOK keys
  - Reboot and enroll keys in UEFI
  - Then install this package
 .
 Supported GPU architectures:
  - Ada Lovelace (H100, L40, RTX 40xx)
  - Hopper (H200)
  - Ampere (A100, A30, RTX 30xx)
  - Turing (T4, RTX 20xx)
  - Volta (V100)
  - Pascal (P100, P40)

Package: cx-gpu-nvidia-datacenter
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 cx-gpu-nvidia
Recommends:
 nvidia-fabricmanager,
 datacenter-gpu-manager,
 nvidia-persistenced
Description: CX Linux NVIDIA Datacenter GPU support
 Extended NVIDIA support for datacenter deployments with
 multi-GPU systems, NVLink, and GPU fabric management.
 .
 Includes:
  - NVIDIA Fabric Manager for NVSwitch systems
  - Datacenter GPU Manager (DCGM) for monitoring
  - NVIDIA Persistence Daemon
